item.description:
A Data Protection Officer is acting in an independent manner.
WHY Article 38(3) establishes some basic protections to help ensure that DPOs are able to perform their tasks with a sufficient degree of autonomy within their organisation. Controllers/processors are required to ensure that the DPO &ldquo;does not receive any instructions regarding the exercise of [his or her] tasks.&rdquo;
What The DPO informs and advise the controller or the processor and the employees who carry out processing of their obligations under the GDPR.
